headline: Week’s Best: SEC Needs White House Approval on Rules
summary: President Donald Trump has issued an executive order that requires independent government agencies such as the Securities and Exchange Commission to seek White House approval before issuing new regulations.  It is part of a broader deregulatory agenda that is running in parallel with efforts by Elon Musk’s Department of Government Efficiency to shrink the size of government.  Ameriprise and LPL locked in legal dispute.
